<h1>Chacteristics of Huskies</h1>
<h2>Personality</h2> 
<p> Huskies are unique in the way that they have both sides of the personality spectrum. They are high energy, have destructive tendincies, playful, mischevious, and loud when they howl. But they are also charming, loving, friendly, gentle, and show kindness to everyone even strangers. 
<h2>Physical</h2>
<p>Huskies are a generally healthy but like all breeds they have certain health risks and are more prone to one disease than another. Some of these diseases is Catarats, Corneal Dystrophy, and Progressive Retinal Atrophy (PRA).These are all conditions related to the health of the eye. Their strong bodies have energy coarsing through it andthey need to be excersiced daily to be kept healthy and happy.
<h2>Feeding</h2>
<p>Although Huskies are big dogs weighing anywhere from 35 to 60 pounds they need a surpringly small amount of food to satisfy their hunger. They need about 2 cups of hig quality dry dog food a day, divided into 2 meals. The higher quality the food the more nutrients being put into your dogs body therefore less needs to be put out at one given time. </p>
<h2>Grooming</h2>
<p>Huskies are an easy breed to care for when it comes to grooming other than one problem, they shed. Although they shed it's not an year round activity so if you can deal with one month twice a year of heavy shedding this might not be a problem for you. This happens because of the temprature change their ancestors experienced in Siberia.</p>
